{"key":"post-6541889","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>6541889</id>\n<content>Those are both the wrong type.  You want calcium carbonate in non-pelletized form, or hydrated lime.  When they say 'safer' than hydrated lime, they mean it's in pellet form so it's slow release.  Hydrated lime is a water soluable powder, so if you use it in your garden, it can kill your plants the next time you water because it all releases at once.  However, that's what we want when putting together a casing layer or bulk sub.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>6542401</next>\n<prev>6541169</prev>\n<first>6541169</first>\n<last>6543694</last>\n<when>1170902541</when>\n<utime>02/08/07 04:42 AM</utime>\n</post>"}